===2010===
[[File:Battle of La Mesa - 2.jpg|thumb|right|Memorial to the [[Battle of La Mesa]]]]
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref name=Census>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0682422|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715033726/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0682422|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA – Vernon city|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Vernon had a population of 112. The population density was {{convert|21.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|people&nbsp;|people|}}. The racial makeup of Vernon was 99 (88.4%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] (51.8% Non-Hispanic White), 4 (3.6%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0 (0%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2 (1.8%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 7 (6%) from [[Race (United States census)|other races]], and 0 (0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 48 persons (42.9%).<ref name="Census" />

The Census reported that 112 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.<ref name="Census" />

There were 28 households, out of which 10 (36%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 13 (46%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 3 (11%) had a female householder with no husband present, 6 (21%) had a male householder with no wife present. There were 1 (9%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnership]] and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 5 households (18%) were made up of individuals, and 2 (7%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 4. There were 22 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (79% of all households); the average family size was 4.<ref name="Census" />

The ages of the population were spread out, with 21 people (19%) under the age of 18, 11 people (10%) aged 18 to 24, 36 people (32%) aged 25 to 44, 30 people (27%) aged 45 to 64, and 14 people (13%) who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 36.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 97.8 males.{{citation needed|date=May 2022}}

There were 29 housing units at an average density of {{convert|5.6|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}},{{citation needed|date=May 2022}} of which 4 (14%) were owner-occupied, and 24 (86%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0%; the rental vacancy rate was 4%. 10 people (9% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 102 people (91%) lived in rental housing units.<ref name="Census" />

According to the 2010 United States census, Vernon had a median household income of $32,188, with 20.0% of the population living below the federal poverty line.{{citation needed|date=May 2022}}

===2000===
[[File:Battle of La Mesa - 7.jpg|thumb|[[Battle of La Mesa|La Mesa Battlefield]] marker]]
The median income for a household in the city was $62,000, and the median income for a family was $62,575. Males had a median income of $46,250, versus $33,750 for females. The per capita income for the city was $17,812. None of the population and none of the families were below the poverty line.

Many of the 112 residents of Vernon were city employees. Many lived in housing owned by the city government. As of 2006, about 44,000 people who work in Vernon daily lived outside of Vernon.<ref name="modelcorr" />

